INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '5754f6b9-d291-4071-8d32-a9082e357d10',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Rails Dev Tooling — Hot Reload, Scaffolding, and CLI Tricks You Should Be Using$escape$,
  $escape$Rails ships with a surprisingly powerful dev tooling surface that most developers underuse. Since Rails 7, `Zeitwerk` handles code reloading automatically — any change to `app/` is picked up without a server restart, governed by `config.enable_reloading` (true by default in development). For views, `ActionController::Live` combined with Turbo Streams gives you real-time UI updates without a full reload cycle.

Scaffolding goes beyond `rails generate scaffold Post title:string body:text`. Use `--no-jbuilder`, `--no-helper`, or `--skip-routes` flags to generate only what you need. Custom generators live in `lib/generators/` and inherit from `Rails::Generators::Base`, letting you codify team conventions into repeatable templates with ERB-based `.tt` files.

The `rails` CLI also exposes `rails notes` (scans TODOs/FIXMEs), `rails routes --grep login` for filtered routing inspection, and `rails runner 'User.find(1).inspect'` for one-off script execution in the app context. Pair `spring` or `bootsnap` for sub-second boot times on large apps.$escape$,
  $escape$# Generate a scaffold, skipping noise
rails generate scaffold Article title:string:index body:text published:boolean \
  --no-jbuilder --no-helper --no-assets

# Custom generator skeleton
# lib/generators/service/service_generator.rb
class ServiceGenerator < Rails::Generators::NamedBase
  source_root File.expand_path('templates', __dir__)

  def create_service_file
    template 'service.rb.tt', "app/services/#{file_name}_service.rb"
  end
end

# Invoke it
rails generate service UserRegistration$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
